  "body": "**Current State:**\r\nWhen you run `tg` w/o any options it creates the folder structure and data as such...\r\n\r\n```\r\n~/.local/share/turbogeth$ tree\r\n.\r\n├── keystore\r\n└── tg\r\n    ├── chaindata\r\n    │   ├── data.mdb\r\n    │   └── lock.mdb\r\n    ├── LOCK\r\n    └── nodekey\r\n\r\n3 directories, 4 files\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Future State:**\r\nWhen you run `tg` w/o options, lets add the network name (i.e. mainnet, rinkeby, etc) to the folder structure, so ppl don't accidentally overwrite `chain.mdb`\r\n\r\n```\r\n/mnt/data/eth$ tree\r\n.\r\n├── mainnet\r\n│   ├── geth.ipc\r\n│   ├── keystore\r\n│   └── tg\r\n│       ├── chaindata\r\n│       │   ├── data.mdb\r\n│       │   └── lock.mdb\r\n│       ├── LOCK\r\n│       ├── nodekey\r\n│       └── nodes\r\n│           ├── data.mdb\r\n│           └── lock.mdb\r\n└── rinkeby\r\n    ├── keystore\r\n    └── tg\r\n        ├── chaindata\r\n        │   ├── data.mdb\r\n        │   └── lock.mdb\r\n        ├── LOCK\r\n        ├── nodekey\r\n        └── nodes\r\n            ├── data.mdb\r\n            └── lock.mdb\r\n\r\n10 directories, 13 files\r\n```",
